# roadmap: git.stage.add + unlimited quota

## phases

### phase 0: factory readiness
- [x] test infra ready (genTempDir + spawnSync pattern)
- [x] no credentials needed (local git operations)
- [x] feedback loops acceptable

### phase 1: git.commit.uses.local.sh
- [ ] add `--stage allow|block` option (parallel to `--push`)
- [ ] change `allow` command to set `uses: "infinite"` (not `999999`)
- [ ] update `get` command to display stage permission
- [ ] update `del`/`block` commands to default stage to "block"
- [ ] add tests for --stage behavior

### phase 2: git.commit.set.sh
- [ ] update `check_uses` to accept `uses === "infinite"` as valid
- [ ] skip decrement when `uses === "infinite"`
- [ ] add test for unlimited no-decrement behavior

### phase 3: git.stage.add.sh
- [ ] create new skill with output.sh reuse
- [ ] implement permission check (stage === "allow")
- [ ] implement global blocker check
- [ ] implement path validation (within repo)
- [ ] implement file existence check
- [ ] implement bounded glob expansion
- [ ] implement fail-fast atomic behavior
- [ ] implement tree-formatted output
- [ ] add tests for all cases

### phase 4: permissions
- [ ] add git.stage.add to init.claude.permissions.jsonc allowlist

## execution order

1. phase 1 → phase 2 → phase 3 → phase 4
2. each phase: implement → test → verify
3. run full test suite before commit

## dependencies

- phase 2 depends on phase 1 (infinite value format)
- phase 3 depends on phase 1 (stage permission field)
- phase 4 depends on phase 3 (skill must exist)

## verification

- [ ] all extant tests pass
- [ ] new tests pass
- [ ] manual verification of typical workflow
